12 (a) (1) (i) An applicant or a licensee is subject to:
13 1. THE REQUIREMENT TO PUT FORTH A GOOD FAITH
14 EFFORT TO MEET the minority business participation goal established for a unit by the
15 Special Secretary for the Office of Small, Minority, and Women Business Affairs under §
16 14–302(a)(1)(ii) of the State Finance and Procurement Article; and
17 (b) (1) The Commission shall ensure that a video lottery operation licensee
18 complies with the requirements of subsection (a)(1) and (2) of this section as a condition of
19 holding the video lottery operation license.
20 (2) The [Governor’s] Office of Small, Minority, and Women Business
21 Affairs shall monitor a licensee’s compliance with subsection (a)(1) and (2) of this section.
22 (3) The [Governor’s] Office of Small, Minority, and Women Business
23 Affairs shall report to the Commission at least every 6 months on the compliance of
24 licensees with subsection (a)(1) and (2) of this section.
25 (4) If the [Governor’s] Office of Small, Minority, and Women Business
26 Affairs reports that a licensee is not in compliance with subsection (a)(1) and (2) of this
27 section, the Commission may take immediate action to ensure the compliance of the
28 licensee.
29 (c) On or after July 1, [2026] 2031, the provisions of subsections (a)(1) and (2)
30 and (b) of this section and any regulations adopted under subsections (a)(1) and (2) and (b)
31 of this section shall be of no effect and may not be enforced.

