22 (a) There is a Governor’s Subcabinet on Socioeconomic Procurement
23 Participation.
24 (b) The Governor’s Subcabinet is composed of:
25 (1) the [Special] Secretary of [the Governor’s Office of Small, Minority, and
26 Women Business Affairs] SOCIAL AND ECONOMIC MOBILITY, who shall serve as chair
27 of the Subcabinet;
28 (2) the Secretary of Budget and Management, or the Secretary’s designee;
29 (3) the Secretary of Commerce, or the Secretary’s designee;
30 (4) the Secretary of General Services, or the Secretary’s designee;
